qas.question: By what is India under the Gupta Empire referered?
What was the time span of the Gupta Empire?
What is the period of the Gupta Empire called?
What philosophy  formed at the time of the Gupta Empire?
What numeral system originated in India?

context: <a0_0>Classical India<a0_0/> refers to the period when much of the Indian subcontinent was reunited under the Gupta Empire (<a1_0>c. 320–550 CE<a1_0/>). This period has been called the <a2_0>Golden Age of India<a2_0/> and was marked by extensive achievements in science, technology, engineering, art, dialectic, literature, logic, mathematics, astronomy, religion, and philosophy that crystallized the elements of what is generally known as <a3_0>Hindu culture<a3_0/>. The <a4_0>Hindu-Arabic<a4_0/> numerals, a positional numeral system, originated in India and was later transmitted to the West through the Arabs. Early Hindu numerals had only nine symbols, until 600 to 800 CE, when a symbol for zero was developed for the numeral system. The peace and prosperity created under leadership of Guptas enabled the pursuit of scientific and artistic endeavors in India.
